    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I think the root of this problem is the swap timer is currently stored in Redux as `secondsRemaining`. I think this organization is really bad, because it requires redux state to be updated every second to decrement the timer, and requires a saga or something to know when to start / stop countdown.\r\n\r\nThis should ideally be stored as a timestamp, and we should do the second countdown in state for timer component.",
